# Alert System Conventions

## Email Delivery

- Gmail SMTP over SSL (port 465) via `smtplib.SMTP_SSL`
- Credentials from env: `SENDER_EMAIL`, `EMAIL_PASSWORD`, `RECIPIENT_EMAIL`
- Kill switch: `ANOMALY_EMAIL_ENABLED` (must be true to send)
- Send as HTML with plain-text fallback (MIME multipart)

## Alert Content

Every alert email must include:
- Underlying ticker and full option contract identifier
- Composite score and full factor breakdown (raw, z-score, weight, contribution per factor)
- Current option price, volume, open interest
- Underlying stock price and % move
- Time since anomaly detected vs. current data lag
- Relevant news headlines (last 24h from Polygon news endpoint)
- Upcoming catalysts if available (earnings date, ex-dividend)

## Deduplication

- Track alerts sent per contract per trading day in the database
- Do not re-alert on the same contract unless composite score increases by 1.0+
- Include "update" label in subject line for score-increase re-alerts

## Error Handling

- Wrap all SMTP operations in try/except; log failures but never crash the pipeline
- Queue failed alerts for retry on next scan cycle (max 3 retries)
- Log every sent/failed/suppressed alert with full context
